      "$\\mathrm{CH}_3-\\mathrm{CH}_2-\\mathrm{CH}_2-\\mathrm{OH}$",
      "<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m6s8c5hc/1b989583-c290-4045-bc8d-51dc62ea5da9/41086c00-e3ed-11ef-88dd-b362bfa8d3ce/file-jaoe38c1m6s8c5hd.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m6s8c5hc/1b989583-c290-4045-bc8d-51dc62ea5da9/41086c00-e3ed-11ef-88dd-b362bfa8d3ce/file-jaoe38c1m6s8c5hd.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"JEE Main 2025 (Online) 23rd January Morning Shift Chemistry - Aldehydes, Ketones and Carboxylic Acids Question 55 English Option 3\">",
      "<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m6s8cmzr/e3d78821-04f0-4f55-87e9-b72c932aa1c0/4e8f6770-e3ed-11ef-88dd-b362bfa8d3ce/file-jaoe38c1m6s8cmzs.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m6s8cmzr/e3d78821-04f0-4f55-87e9-b72c932aa1c0/4e8f6770-e3ed-11ef-88dd-b362bfa8d3ce/file-jaoe38c1m6s8cmzs.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"JEE Main 2025 (Online) 23rd January Morning Shift Chemistry - Aldehydes, Ketones and Carboxylic Acids Question 55 English Option 4\">"
    ],
    "solution": "<p>This is an example of Tollen's reaction i.e. multiple cross aldol followed by cross Cannizaro reaction</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m7erb0nl/99dc30d1-0017-458e-bb69-1e6324affcb0/ad3c8810-f050-11ef-a864-2d89966ea2d7/file-jaoe38c1m7erb0nm.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m7erb0nl/99dc30d1-0017-458e-bb69-1e6324affcb0/ad3c8810-f050-11ef-a864-2d89966ea2d7/file-jaoe38c1m7erb0nm.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"JEE Main 2025 (Online) 23rd January Morning Shift Chemistry - Aldehydes, Ketones and Carboxylic Acids Question 55 English Explanation\"></p>",
