    "_id": "6a2bdc992762cf4b576a0c17",
    "question_id": "m6qlldm9",
    "chapterId": "reactions-involving-aldehydes",
    "subject": "Chemistry",
    "topic": "reactions-involving-aldehydes",
    "difficulty": "medium",
    "marks": 4,
    "tags": [],
    "options": [],
    "solution": "<p>Mass of benzaldehyde = 5.3 g</p>\n<p>Mass of product = 3.51 g</p>\n<p>Claisen - Schmidt reaction :</p>\n<p>Condensation of aromatic aldehydes / ketones (without alpha-hydrogen) with diphatic aldehydes /ketones (with alpha-hydrogen) in the presence of weak base to form $\\alpha,\\beta$-unsaturated aldehydes/ketones.</p>\n<p>Given</p>\n<p>benzaldehyde $\\to$ dibenzalacetone</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m7pxnkpr/dbd9b06b-373f-4df4-a408-223bc1977b13/205c52f0-f676-11ef-a190-1be9b7c3bee4/file-jaoe38c1m7pxnkps.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m7pxnkpr/dbd9b06b-373f-4df4-a408-223bc1977b13/205c52f0-f676-11ef-a190-1be9b7c3bee4/file-jaoe38c1m7pxnkps.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"JEE Main 2025 (Online) 29th January Evening Shift Chemistry - Aldehydes, Ketones and Carboxylic Acids Question 60 English Explanation\"></p>\n<p>Formula of percent yield</p>\n<p>Percent yield $$ = {{actual\\,yield} \\over {Theoretical\\,yield}} \\times 100$$</p>\n<p>Actual yield = 3.51 g</p>\n<p>From the reaction, the stoichiometric ratio between benzaldehyde and dibenzal acetone is 2 : 1</p>\n<p>benzaldehyde : dibenzalacetone</p>\n<p>$$2:1$$</p>\n<p>$$1:{1 \\over 2}$$</p>\n<p>Moles of benzaldehyde:</p>\n<p>$$Moles = {{Mass} \\over {Molar\\,mass}}$$</p>\n<p>$$ = {{5.3\\,g} \\over {106.12\\,g/mol}}$$</p>\n<p>= 0.04994 mol</p>\n<p>Molarmass of benzaldehyde = 106.12 g/mol</p>\n<p>For 1 mole of benzaldehyde, $\\frac{1}{2}$ moles product (dibenzalacetone) is formed.</p>\n<p>So, for 0.04994 mol benzaldehyde, $\\frac{1}{2}\\times0.04994$ mol dibenzalacetone is formed.</p>\n<p>So, moles of dibenzalacetone = 0.02497 mol</p>\n<p>Mass of product dibenzalacetone (Theoretical yield)</p>\n<p>Mass = moles $\\times$ molarmass</p>\n<p>$=0.02497$ mol $\\times$ $234.29$ g/mol</p>\n<p>= 5.850 g</p>\n<p>Percent yield $$ = {{3.51\\,g} \\over {5.85\\,g}} \\times 100$$</p>\n<p>$$ = 0.6 \\times 100 = 60\\% $$</p>",
    "__v": 0,
    "title": "JEE Main 2025 (Online) 29th January Evening Shift",
    "exam": "JEE Main"
  },
